'From Squeak3.10.2 of ''5 June 2008'' [latest update: #7179] on 8 November 2009 at 10:15:58 am'!"Change Set:		SecureUserDirectoryMijibakeFix-muDate:			8 November 2009Author:			Masashi UmezawaA quick fix of SecurityManager>>secureUserDirectory for not creating mojibake user directory when Squeak runs on a multibyte-named directory."!!SecurityManager methodsFor: 'accessing' stamp: 'mu 11/8/2009 10:04'!secureUserDirectory	"SecurityManager default secureUserDirectory"	| dir |	dir := self primSecureUserDirectory.	dir := dir		ifNil: [FileDirectory default pathName]		ifNotNil: [(FilePath pathName: dir isEncoded: true) asSqueakPathName].			((dir isWideString and: [SmalltalkImage current platformName = 'Win32']) 		and: [LanguageEnvironment win32VMUsesUnicode]) ifTrue:[^FileDirectory default pathName].			^dir! !